- 'healing time' refers to the time taken to resolve bugs, calculated as the difference between resolved date and reported date; 
- 'disease' refers to bugs; 
- 'disease severity' refers to the severity level of the bug; 
- 'treatment type' refers to the resolution type.

sql:
SELECT subtotal
  FROM bug_severity_counts
  WHERE resolution_type_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- A "resolved bug" refers to a bug that has been successfully fixed and closed; 
- "Average resolution time" is a measure of how quickly a user resolves bugs on average, calculated by summing up the time taken to resolve each bug and dividing by the total number of bugs resolved; 
- The ranking is based on the average resolution time, with the fastest resolver being the one who resolves bugs in the shortest time on average.

sql:
SELECT AVG(julianday(resolved_date) - julianday(reported_date)) AS total_average_time_to_resolution
FROM bugs
WHERE status = 'Resolved';
